<doc id="209651" wikidata="Q12214029" url="?curid=209651" title="Rheidae">
<text>Rheidae is a family of flightless ratite birds which first appeared in the Paleocene. It is today represented by the sole living genus &quot;Rhea&quot;, but also contains several extinct genera.

==Taxonomy==
Order Rheiformes [Rheimorphae ; Rheae ]
* Family †Opisthodactylidae 
** Genus ?†&quot;Diogenornis&quot; (Late Paleocene) – possibly a member of Casuariiformes instead.
** Genus †&quot;Opisthodactylus&quot; (Miocene) – rheid?
* Family Rheidae 
** Genus †&quot;Heterorhea&quot; (Pliocene)
** Genus †&quot;Hinasuri&quot; 
** Genus &quot;Rhea&quot; 

