<doc id="209662" wikidata="Q4974502" url="?curid=209662" title="Brooke family">
<text>The Brooke family is an English family that ruled the Raj of Sarawak, from 1841 until 1 July, 1946, when Charles Vyner Brooke, the third and last &quot;White Rajah&quot; ceded Sarawak to the British Empire due to the lack of resources to finance reconstruction after World War II.

Rajahs of Sarawak:
*James Brooke (1841–1868)
*Charles Brooke (1868–1917)
*Charles Vyner Brooke (1917–1946)

